Name: Dauphin Lt. Col W.G. Billy Barker VC
Edmonton International
Deice Info:
DEICE/ANTI-ICE: 

TYPE IV Available at FBO (Airside) for hangar spray
•	Fluid used is Cryotech Polar Guard Advance
•	Give as much notice as possible to FBO of request.
•	Pax permitted to load in hangar after spray completed.
•	If aircraft arriving need deice prior to type IV application, will take 2-3 hours under radiant heater in hangar to dry off, so for in and out trips during snow events use the CDF - info below.


CDF Info: 

•	Type 1 and Type 4 available
•	30 minutes prior to departure contact Edmonton De-Ice on 122.85 to request de-ice with following information:
·	Flight Number
·	AC Type
·	Fluids Required
-       Surfaces to be de-iced
Edmonton Deice will assign a deicing facility and provide expected que times. All de-ice ops are performed with engines running unless advised by iceman. AC should be configured for deicing prior to positioning on deice bay. For more info please contact de-ice manager @ 780.710.8546
